My true Self? My fake Self?

253
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,480
You are you.

254
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,950
There is little difference between
how you interpret yourself

255
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:03,360
and how others interpret you.

256
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,560
Right.

257
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:07,960
My clothes... My shoes... My room...

258
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:10,730
These all are parts of what
makes up my Self.

259
00:10:10,730 --> 00:10:13,460
These things are connected through
your consciousness.

260
00:10:14,170 --> 00:10:16,360
So, what I think is me, is me.

261
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:19,230
What I recognize as Self is myself.

262
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:21,670
But I don't understand my Self.

263
00:10:22,170 --> 00:10:24,180
Where am I?

264
00:10:24,180 --> 00:10:25,670
What am I?

265
00:10:26,210 --> 00:10:27,700
What am I?

266
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:29,750
THAT'S WHY YOU CLOSE YOUR SOUL

267
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,810
Nobody understands me!

268
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:36,650
What are you, stupid? Of course
nobody understands you!

269
00:10:37,390 --> 00:10:40,050
Nobody can ever understand you.

270
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:42,190
The only one who can
take care of you

271
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:45,560
and understand you
is you, yourself.

272
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,830
So, you must take care of yourself.

273
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:51,970
But I still don't understand my Self!

274
00:10:51,970 --> 00:10:53,640
I don't even know what it is
that makes me myself!

275
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,070
How could I love myself?!

276
00:10:55,070 --> 00:10:56,280
HE IS INSECURE

277
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,740
You are still unstable.

278
00:10:58,740 --> 00:11:00,350
That is, the present you.

279
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:03,010
And the people around
the present you.

280
00:11:03,010 --> 00:11:05,480
And the environment that surrounds
the present you.

281
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:09,390
None of these last forever.

282
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:11,690
Time continues to flow,
and time brings change.

283
00:11:11,690 --> 00:11:14,720
Your world is in a state
of constant change.

284
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:19,960
You are capable of change anytime.
Your Mind perceives these changes.

285
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,630
What is this?

286
00:11:21,630 --> 00:11:23,370
A world of nothing?

287
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:25,240
A world with nobody in it?

288
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,110
This is the world of perfect freedom.

289
00:11:27,110 --> 00:11:28,770
Freedom?

290
00:11:28,770 --> 00:11:32,710
A world of perfect freedom, a world
in which you have no restrictions.

291
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,280
Is this really freedom?

292
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:37,880
Yes, this is what it is.

293
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:40,220
However, this world
has nothing in it.

294
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:41,990
Unless I do something?

295
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:44,760
Right, unless you do or
think of something.

296
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,220
But...

297
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:48,360
I don't know what to do or think!

298
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,560
He is uncertain.

299
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:51,600
He has no image of Self
to orient himself.

300
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,400
There's nothing solid here.

301
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,200
It is a world in which there
are no obstacles.

302
00:11:55,710 --> 00:11:56,880
THIS IS FREEDOM

303
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,600
This is a world in which you can
do anything you wish.

304
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,830
But you're afraid, aren't you?

305
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:05,010
Don't you know what it is
that you want to do?

306
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:06,640
What should I do?

307
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:08,250
