top and bottom.

309
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:13,850
But you've lost a degree
of your freedom.

310
00:12:13,850 --> 00:12:16,550
Now you must stand on the ground.

311
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:19,020
But now you feel easier, don't you?

312
00:12:19,020 --> 00:12:21,660
You have less to trouble your mind.

313
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:23,190
And now, you can walk.

314
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:25,200
This is happening because
you will it to be.

315
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,470
Is this my will?

316
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:31,550
This world with the floor is the
only thing around yourself.

317
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:34,490
But now, you can move around
anywhere you wish to within it.

318
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:37,620
You could even turn the world
upside down, if you wanted to.

319
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:41,660
And the position of your world
is not the same either.

320
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:44,660
It changes with the passage of time.

321
00:12:44,660 --> 00:12:47,130
You can change yourself as well.

322
00:12:47,730 --> 00:12:49,500
What forms your shape is your mind

323
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:52,730
and its interaction with the world
that surrounds you.

324
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:56,010
You can do anything here,
because this is your world.

325
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:59,110
This is the shape of your reality.

326
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:00,280
THIS IS THE REALITY

327
00:13:01,350 --> 00:13:02,810
What is this?

328
00:13:02,810 --> 00:13:04,680
An empty space.

329
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:06,170
An empty world.

330
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,740
A world where nothing
exists but myself.

331
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:12,390
With only myself, I have nothing
to interact with.

332
00:13:12,390 --> 00:13:14,960
It's as if I'm here, but
not here at all.

333
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:17,290
It's as if I'm slowly fading
out of existence.

334
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,130
WHY?

335
00:13:18,430 --> 00:13:20,970
Because only you are here.

336
00:13:20,970 --> 00:13:22,670
Only myself?

337
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:24,870
Without others to interact with,

338
00:13:24,870 --> 00:13:27,740
you cannot truly recognize
your own image.

339
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:28,930
My own image?

340
00:13:28,930 --> 00:13:30,310
MY IMAGE?

341
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:35,040
Yes. In the act of observing others,
you may recognize yourself.

342
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:37,680
Your image of yourself is restrained

343
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:40,150
by having to observe the barriers
between yourself and others.

344
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:44,060
And yet, you can not see yourself
without the presence of others.

345
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:47,160
When there are others, I can
perceive myself as an individual.

346
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,920
If I am alone, then I will be the
same as everything else.

347
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,560
There will be no difference between
myself and nothing!

348
00:13:53,260 --> 00:13:55,800
By recognizing the differences
between yourself and others,

349
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,670
you establish your identity
as yourself.

350
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:01,370
The very first other person
is your mother.

351
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:04,680
Your mother is a different individual.

352
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:06,910
